Homosexuality has not been considered illegal in China since 1997, but discrimination against LGBT people is widespread.
Studies estimate that because of conservative perceptions in the country, 70-90% of men who have sex with men eventually get married to women.
The transmission of the virus often occurs due to inappropriate sexual protection in such relationships.
In 2003, the Chinese government promised universal access to HIV drugs as part of a plan to address the problem.
